{
  "texts": [
    "To this purpose intermediaries must implement reasonable duties of care, proportional to their resources and risks posed to society, including a duty to cooperate with audits (Recital 40).VLOPs must commission annual audits by accredited entities to assess compliance with obligations related to risk management systems (Article 26), content moderation processes (Article 15), algorithmic systems (Article 29), and advertising transparency (Articles 24, 30) (Article 28).",
    "Audit summaries containing key methodologies, findings and recommendations must be published, while preserving trade secrets (Article 37).",
    "The European Commission and national Digital Service Coordinators can request additional ad-hoc external audits on issues of concern (Article 33).Targeted internal audits are also imposed focusing specifically on ad transparency (Article 24) and risk assessments (Article 35).",
    "Audit findings may inform future regulatory interventions or enforcement actions if systemic non-compliance is uncovered (Article 35).However, audits are limited to assessing procedural compliance rather than evaluating substantive fairness, proportionality or effectiveness (Recital 92).",
    "The level of genuine independence between powerful platforms and auditors also remains unclear (Article 37)."
  ]
}